        "jobDescription": "Job DescriptionJob Description\n<p>\n \n  Sr. Data Visualization and Reporting Analyst\n \n</p>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n The Data Visualization and Reporting Analyst is responsible for building automated, actionable and accurate reporting dashboards for the Enterprise Platforms and Infrastructure organization. The successful candidate collaborates closely with cross functional stakeholders, data analysts, data architects, and data engineers to design, develop, and continuously enhance dashboard content, functionality, and performance.\n</p>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n \n  YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES\n \n</p>\n<p>\n The primary responsibilities of this role, Senior Data Visualization and Reporting Analyst, are to:\n</p>\n<ul>\n <li>\n  Build automated, actionable, and accurate reporting dashboards\n </li>\n <li>\n  Collect and interpret requirements and translate them into data visualizations\n </li>\n <li>\n  Analyze current data, build models to both explain trends and create dashboards that accurately reflect the current state\n </li>\n <li>\n  Build wireframes, mock-ups, and ad-hoc visualizations; review them with stakeholders; ensure alignment with requirements\n </li>\n <li>\n  Collaborate closely with cross functional stakeholders, data analysts, data architects, and data engineers to develop design prototypes and continuously enhance dashboard content, functionality, and performance\n </li>\n <li>\n  Recommend and implement automation of reporting; identify and implement opportunities to streamline and improve processes\n </li>\n <li>\n  Continuously and proactively identify opportunities to improve data quality and work collaboratively across teams to recommend changes to processes, policies, and source systems that improve data integrity\n </li>\n <li>\n  Assist in driving business intelligence adoption throughout the organization\n </li>\n <li>\n  Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements: automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability, etc.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Build analytics tools that utilize the data pipeline to provide actionable insights into customer experience, operational efficiency and other key business performance metrics.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Work with data and analytics experts to strive for greater functionality in our data systems.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n \n  WHO YOU ARE\n \n</p>\n<p>\n Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:\n</p>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n \n  Required Qualifications:\n \n</p>\n<ul>\n <li>\n  Bachelor's degree with at least 3 years of relevant experience or at least 5 years of applicable data reporting and analysis experience or equivalent.\n </li>\n <li>\n  At least 3 years' experience using SQL in a data reporting and analysis role, including proficiency in writing queries and data wrangling skills\n </li>\n <li>\n  At least 3 years' experience building business-focused visualizations and user interfaces\n </li>\n <li>\n  Skilled in creating data visualizations using business intelligence software, ideally with experience in Power BI, Spotfire, or Tableau\n </li>\n <li>\n  Experience working with data sets in various conditions/formats and which require building relationships across disparate data sources to create a comprehensive data model\n </li>\n <li>\n  Skilled in cleaning, standardizing, filtering, and transforming data to create datasets ready to be analyzed and displayed graphically\n </li>\n <li>\n  Understands what makes for a compelling visualization, can tell a story using data, and can draw insights from large datasets\n </li>\n <li>\n  Experience with object-oriented/object function scripting languages such as Python, Java, C++, Scala, etc.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Understand transactional systems, data modeling, data flow, data wrangling, and data automation and provisioning\n </li>\n <li>\n  Experience with a modern data stack, including tools like Snowflake and Trifacta\n </li>\n <li>\n  Ability to logically and efficiently structure ambiguous problems, identify sources of data, conduct complicated analysis, identify key insights and recommend actions\n </li>\n <li>\n  Ability to query and analyze data from disparate data sources\n </li>\n <li>\n  Demonstrated track record of prioritizing, multitasking, and managing multiple projects/assignments simultaneously in a fast-paced environment with tight deadlines\n </li>\n <li>\n  Working knowledge of building and optimizing ?big data? data pipelines, architectures and data sets.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Strong analytic skills related to working with structured and unstructured datasets.\n </li>\n <li>\n  A successful history of manipulating, processing and extracting value from large and disconnected datasets.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Working knowledge of message queuing, stream processing, and highly scalable ?big data? data stores.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Sound project management and organizational skills.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Ability to work collaboratively across functions, geographies, and organizational levels to develop solutions; engages and involves key stakeholders\n </li>\n <li>\n  Experience supporting and working with cross-functional teams in a dynamic environment.\n </li>\n <li>\n  Strong analytical and data interpretation skills\n </li>\n <li>\n  Excellent written and verbal communication skills\n </li>\n <li>\n  Strong functional knowledge of IT services such as application support and development and computer/infrastructure services;\n </li>\n <li>\n  Strong collaboration and partnering skills; Thorough understanding of Bayer business objectives and environment; Clearly and effectively conveys and/or presents information verbally; Excellent inter-cultural understanding and experience.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n BAY1JP00016234\n</p>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>\n<p>\n <br />\n</p>",
