        "OBJdesc": "The objective of this position is to support and promote product profitability for AM xEV Business Unit The position will develop and track financial reports to report to AM management as well as reporting for Japan. This position will require collaboration with multiple sites and groups within the Business Unit.\n<br>\nMinimum Qualifications (Education, Experience, and Skills):\n \n\n\n \n  4-Year college degree in Finance, Engineering, Engineering Technology, Business, or similar curriculum of study\n \n \n  Knowledge of computer systems (specifically Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint) to perform and present analysis for necessary job duties\n \n \n  Strong written and verbal communication skills to crate and present concepts to internal teams and all levels of management\n \n\n\n \n  Preferred Qualifications (Education, Experience, and Skills):\n \n\n\n \n  2+ Years' experience working with finance and accounting specifically looking at profit and loss statements, standard costing, and cash flow analysis\n \n \n  Experience in working in a multicultural business environment\n \n \n  Previous experience in SQL, INFOR or other database applications\n \n \n  Budget management experience\n \n\n\n \n  Position Duties and Responsibilities:\n \n\n\n \n  Description of Duties and Responsibilities\n \n\n\n \n  Weight of Importance %\n \n\n\n Review and analyze profit by product reporting for sites/products -\n \n  30%\n \n\n\n Gap analysis and presentation of costs from budget and original target -\n \n  20%\n \n\n\n Support countermeasure actions and work to resolve gaps and track progress for regional initiatives -\n \n  20%\n \n\n\n xEV new business project management support -\n \n  10%\n \n\n\n Collaboration with Japan to review monthly targets and reporting -\n \n  10%\n \n\n\n Other duties as assigned -\n \n  10%\n \n\n\n \n  Skills and Abilities:\n \n\n\n \n  Ability to develop strong working relationship both internally and with customers\n \n \n  High ethical standards\n \n \n  Ability to work independently and support findings with data\n \n \n  Critical Thinking -Using logic and reasoning to identify the strengths and weaknesses of alternative solutions, conclusions or approaches to problems\n \n \n  Problem Solving - Reviewing related information to identifying problems, develop and evaluate options and implement solutions\n \n \n  Judgment and Decision Making - Considering the relative costs and benefits of potential actions to choose the most appropriate one\n \n \n  Collaborations with different job functions and levels of management\n \n \n  Analyze data and find insights to improve constitution\n \n\n\n \n  Software:\n \n\n\n \n  Proficiency in Excel &amp; PowerPoint\n \n \n  Experience in Power BI\n \n\n\n \n  Essential to Job Functions - Physical and/or Mental Restrictions:\n \n\n\n · Ability to work for long periods of time while sitting\n\n\n · Ability to lift and/or move up to 25 pounds\n\n\n · Visual ability to work accurately with detailed information and a computer screen\n\n\n \n  Work Environment - Travel, Noise, Smells, Quiet, Indoors or Outdoors, etc.\n \n\n\n \n  Requires up to 25% travel\n \n \n  2-3 days working in the reporting location\n \n \n  Office setting environment, with occasional visit to production facilities\n \n \n  Requires night meetings to collaborate with overseas bases\n \n\n\n \n  Equipment Used\n \n\n\n \n  Personal Computer, cellular phone, company vehicle",
