        "OBJdesc": "The Business Analyst evaluates business processes, identifies needs and develops strategies to maximize the accuracy and efficiency of products and services for internal and external project initiatives. The Business Analyst may work with internal customers, external end users as well as channel partners to integrate RMS solutions with client systems. The Business Analyst will demonstrate advanced knowledge of product functionality and the back-end systems and technologies supporting RMS client offerings.\n<br>\nDuties and Responsibilities\n \n\n\n\n\n · Perform business, technical and user requirement analysis for new product and process improvements\n\n\n · Collect and analyze data for improved business processes and potential business expansion\n\n\n · Lead projects and coordinate with stakeholders to produce better business outcomes\n\n\n · Serve as technical liaison between development teams and non-technical stakeholders, both internal and external\n\n\n · Assist in defining project scope, impact, outcome criteria and metrics\n\n\n · Analyze customer-supplied specifications for completeness and accuracy\n\n\n · Manage requirements throughout the project lifecycle, assuring fulfillment and/or redefining as necessary\n\n\n · Create product and process documentation for both current and future states\n\n\n · Perform ad-hoc SQL reporting\n\n\n · Additional duties and responsibilities as assigned\n\n\n\n\n \n  Qualifications\n \n\n\n\n\n · Excellent listening, interpersonal, written, and verbal communication skills\n\n\n · Great analytical, critical thinking and problem-solving abilities\n\n\n · Strong adaptability and capacity to work in a fast-paced environment\n\n\n · Logical and efficient, with keen attention to detail\n\n\n · Highly self-motivated and directed\n\n\n · Strong customer service orientation\n\n\n · Experience working in a team-oriented, collaborative environment\n\n\n · In-depth understanding of organizational data flow and its use in management decision making\n\n\n · SQL experience and knowledge required\n\n\n · Data analysis, trending and mining experience preferred\n\n\n · Knowledge of the healthcare claims process and revenue cycle preferred\n\n\n · Knowledge of ANSI X 12 Health Care transaction sets, including 837s and 835s, strongly desired\n\n\n · Experience in an Agile software development lifecycle desired\n <br>\n\n\n \n  Education/Experience\n \n\n\n\n\n Bachelor’s Degree OR High School Diploma (GED) with a minimum 3 years relevant experience required.\n\n\n <br>\n\nCompany DescriptionFounded in 2006, Revenue Management Solutions has a bold mission to change the healthcare technology landscape by delivering innovative solutions to help solve the complex challenges facing our customers. Our pursuit of this mission is the driving force that brings us to work each day. We believe in embracing new ideas, challenging ourselves and failing forward. We have assembled a team and created a culture where we respect and celebrate individual talents and team wins. With 15+ years in the business of Healthcare Remittance Processing, RMS has continued to advance the Healthcare Revenue Cycle with automated solutions that have put us at the top of our field. If you are looking to join a team where your work can be personally and professionally rewarding, don’t just join a company with a mission. Join a mission with a company behind it.",
